                            <comment id="14900053" author="michael-o" created="Sun, 20 Sep 2015 20:15:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maven 2.2.1 is retired. So closing as won&apos;t fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14900058" author="dennisl@apache.org" created="Sun, 20 Sep 2015 20:27:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t expect us to make this work for Maven 2, but we should at least document the currently behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14900247" author="michael-o" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2015 06:11:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is that still true for Maven 3? I am cofused why we need to document a behavior which is not present in Maven 3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14902639" author="dennisl@apache.org" created="Tue, 22 Sep 2015 13:43:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Even though Maven 2.2.1 is now EOL, that doesn&apos;t mean that people stop using it straight away.&lt;br/&gt;
This plugin does not yet require Maven 3. To be nice to those users out there who try to use the inline configuration option with Maven 2, we should document that it only works for Maven 3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14902645" author="michael-o" created="Tue, 22 Sep 2015 13:45:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I do agree.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14942774" author="dennisl@apache.org" created="Sun, 4 Oct 2015 19:10:23 +0000"  >&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Document the behavior&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Do not run ITs that uses inline configuration unless the Maven version is 3+&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
